reviews.text: A bit expensive but the quality doesn’t fit

The Sun Chui wet market redevelopment, which has kept the area inaccessible for some 9-12 months, totally sucks! 

## Here is an overview:
*Florist & plant shop          = GONE
*Electrical & lighting shop = GONE
*South Asian general goods & liquor shop = GONE
*Butcher Shop = GONE
*Dim sum snacks & waffle shop = GONE
*Funeral & festivals supplies shop = GONE
*Fruit & vegetables shop × about 2 = GONE

## Newly added:
*Restaurant -a type that the area already has several of
*More supermarket

## In summary, it's OUT with variety and utility and IN with more of the same. 😒
Staff is somewhat helpful. Food choices are somewhat acceptable.
Average food, average price. Don't expect too much. Enough to fill you up.
Fine for just a meal.

result.name: Sun Chui Shopping Centre

reviews.text: Great shopping centre , plenty of food and convenience stores. Great variety of traditional and big chain restaurants
All u want still have, so far so good
Enough light make the place peaceful

It is a small local shopping center; good enough for local community. 
Some good restaurants, MacDonald, Pizza Hut, Doctor's Chambers, Shop for many house hold products are here. 

There is one MTR discount machine also here. You can punch your Octopus and get $2 discount in next trip from Tai Wai Station to anywhere.
Toilets hygiene not really in a good situation.

result.name: 美心MX

reviews.text: 連鎖快餐店美心做得唔錯，價錢唔貴，冷氣夠凍，尤其下午茶更抵食
海南雞飯不錯，但另一個豆腐飯酸咗…

近新開的美心快餐，在吧枱位置都有很貼心的設計，顧客可以在此邊吃飯，邊為手機充電！

要了一個龍蝦汁青口扁意粉，味道尚算不錯！
質素可以,不過份量較為少.
不知為何？新翠美心食L1要29元，在港澳碼头食25元？
